15:
Scoundrel! I shan't tolerate more
unruly behavior!
18: You shall not pass! Not before me!
36: Let's get out of here, guys!
43:
*pant* Did we lose them? Because I
dunno how much longer I can keep
going like this...
47:
It seems like the poppets aren't
following. Perhaps they can't leave
the town's boundary...
57:
J-just peachy! Why? What's with the
worried looks?
62:
Please, don't take Simon's words to
heart. We don't have proof that he
was telling the truth yet.
69: What even is the truth anymore?
73:
Everyone's told me completely
different things, and I'm just so
confused about it all!
77:
I understand how you must feel.
Even I, the great Razelt, cannot tell
what the facts are.
80:
But if you can trust no one
statements, why not search out the
truth yourself?
88:
The ruins of Mosnia's capital lie just
outside this forest.
91:
We should be able to find the
Mosnian coat of arms etched into
the architecture and compare it to
the one that's in your letters.
96:
In any case, let's make camp here
for tonight, and you can think on
what you wish to do.
105: Prika? Why are you still awake?
113:
Ah... Just had a few things on my
mind...
120:
I promised to stick by your side
when we're out here.
123: Oh... You sure did, didn't you?
127:
Wait, OUT here? Outside?! I didn't
even realize... with everything that
happened...
129:
These woods are kind of amazing.
They feel so alive, even at night, huh?
131:
Yes. I felt the same way when I first
camped out.
135:
I saw a black blob go flying out of
the trees earlier! I wonder what kind
of bird it was!
139:
Perhaps it was a bug. Bugs can fly
too.
142:
Hmm, like a rhino beetle? They can
fly, right? That's so cool! I've never
seen one before!
146:
Those letters you're holding... Are
they the ones you received from
your prince?
150:
Yeah, I... I brought them with me
when I left the castle. I don't know
why.
153:
He seems to have been an
important pen pal of yours.
156:
A pen pal? I've never thought of it
that way before, but now that you
mention it...
159:
You know, I always looked forward to
his letters.
161:
I created the town and spruced up
the castle just for the day he'd come
visit.
165:
Grey used to worry that I'd get
bored, but honestly I was so busy
that I never had a moment to relax!
168:
You did a good job. The castle was
beautiful.
172:
Right? I had no idea when he'd show
up, so I kept everything in tip-top
shape!
175:
...But if Mosnia was already gone this
whole time... That means the prince
was never real. Our friendship? Poof.
Never existed.
181:
If something never existed, it was
never there in the first place. But
that's not the case here, is it?
185:
I mean, I guess? We definitely
exchanged conversations in our
lettersI didn't imagine that, so...
187:
Huh... You're right. Just because
Mosnia isn't real, doesn't mean the
prince isn't.
192:
I've made up my mind! I'm going to
check out those ruins!
200:
Hey, Stella? Next time, you should tell
me about the place you live! That,
um... Starview? Starview Village?
203:
I'm not that good at talking, but I will
do my best.
207:
It's kind of been a dream of mine to
chat like this. Just us and the stars...
211:
Minus all the bad stuff that got us
here, of course!
218:
You're up for it? Awesome! Let's blab
the night away!
